The paper deals with the computational problem of computing the edit distance between a pair of strings, which is a fundamental problem in computer science. The paper presents two streaming algorithms for computing edit distance, which suggests that it belongs to the sub-category of data structures (cs.DS) and algorithms (cs.DM). The paper also mentions that the running time does not depend on the alphabet size, which suggests that it belongs to the sub-category of information theory (cs.IT). The paper uses techniques from linear algebra and matrix multiplication, which suggests that it belongs to the sub-category of computational complexity (cs.CC). Finally, the paper presents experimental results and discusses the practical implementation of the algorithms, which suggests that it belongs to the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG).
